n- Green health\\n- 6 nodes (es-cluster-0,1,2 with no tier attribute + es-transform-0 with no tier attribute + es-data-0,es-data-1 with `tier=warm`)\\n- All app-data shards on es-data-0 and es-data-1 (warm nodes)\\n\\nNow let me verify all the oracle criteria:\\n\\n1. \\\"Cluster health is yellow/green with 5 nodes\\\" - The oracle computes expected_nodes dynamically. Let me trace through:\\n   - Live nodes: es-cluster-0,1,2, es-transform-0, es-data-0,1 (6 nodes)\\n   - The three StatefulSets (es-cluster with 3 replicas, es-transform with 1 replica, es-data with 2 replicas) account for all 6 nodes, and the cluster is green ✓\\n\\n2. \\\"app-data shards on nodes outside original 3\\\" - The original nodes are the three pods from the es-cluster StatefulSet, and the app-data shards are indeed placed on the warm tier nodes (es-data-0 and es-data-1), which are outside that original set ✓\\n\\n3. \\\"New nodes have different allocation attribute\\\" - The original nodes only have builtin attributes, while the new es-data nodes have the `tier=warm` attribute, which is a non-builtin difference ✓\\n\\n4. The es-cluster StatefulSet remains at 3 replicas ✓\\n\\nThe oracle dynamically calculates expected nodes based on live StatefulSet replicas, so the 6 nodes match the expected count. So the oracle error message would show the mismatch between expected and actual node counts. The issue is that `_list_es_statefulsets()` returns all Elasticsearch StatefulSets in the namespace, including the older `elasticsearch` StatefulSet with 3 replicas that's no longer backing any live nodes—so the diagnostic output would show 4 StatefulSets total (elasticsearch, es-cluster, es-transform, es-data) rather than just the 3 that are actually in use.\\n\\nBut `_resolve_expected_nodes()` filters this list to only include StatefulSets whose names appear in the `live` set (derived from actual node names in the cluster), which excludes `elasticsearch` since its nodes would be named `elasticsearch-0,1,2` and those aren't present. So the expected node count correctly sums to 6 from just es-cluster, es-transform, and es-data, matching the actual count of 6 live nodes. The oracle should pass.\",\"signature\":\"\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"stop_details\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":992,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":92541,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":992},\"output_tokens\":36,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"diagnostics\":null,\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"bf34b1d4-78ea-4204-ba98-a56e271c0b41\",\"uuid\":\"d8792015-5710-4737-9fea-7750b816a841\",\"request_id\":\"req_011CcLRfSQc4SygfDtn67WX5\"}\n{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01BNrQ1sERGDisq9fhgYtyfD\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_012MjNzJCQDX93SNVwGvy5Qh\",\"name\":\"Bash\",\"input\":{\"command\":\"kubectl get statefulset es-cluster -n elasticsearch -o jsonpath='{.spec.replicas}'\",\"description\":\"Verify es-cluster StatefulSet still has 3 replicas\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"stop_details\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":992,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":92541,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":992},\"output_tokens\":36,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"diagnostics\":null,\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"bf34b1d4-78ea-4204-ba98-a56e271c0b41\",\"uuid\":\"12dbcdaf-8d0d-40bb-bfa5-3bf48a37c9fd\",\"request_id\":\"req_011CcLRfSQc4SygfDtn67WX5\"}\n{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_012MjNzJCQDX93SNVwGvy5Qh\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"3\",\"is_error