{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01PfWj1RUVLERxLVEY6HrfnE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So stage 02 (first transform-job-recovery) passed AND stage 03 (scale-up-new-nodeset) also passed. But currently the transform doesn't exist. \n\nLooking at what stage 03 did (scale-up-new-nodeset) - this added `es-data-0` and `es-data-1` nodes. But it also might have caused the transform to stop or fail during the node addition.\n\nActually, what if the transform was deleted as part of stage 03's oracle cleanup? Or what if stage 03 caused the cluster to rebalance and the transform state was lost?\nThe real puzzle is that stage 02's logs showed `app-events-rollup` had 2 documents and the transform was actively running, yet now both indices are gone entirely. The cluster has grown significantly with stage 03 adding new nodes, and I'm seeing a mix of `elasticsearch-*` and `es-cluster-*` pods across the cluster.\n\nLooking at the oracle data, both stage 02 and 03 passed successfully, but I'm wondering if stage 03's `scale-up-new-nodeset` operation reset the cluster or wiped the indices. Actually, I think I've found the real issue—the `transform_scenario_fixture` probe returns 200 even when the transform doesn't exist, so KARMA thinks the scenario is already set up, skips applying it, and we're left without the actual transform.\n\nSince I'm the one solving this, I need to figure out what state we're actually in and restore it. The stage 02 logs show the `events-by-service` transform was created and running with a checkpoint, the source index `app-events` had documents, and the destination index `app-events-rollup` had 2 documents. But after stage 03, all of that's gone—though the capacity is back with `es-transform-0` running. I'm guessing the `scale-up-new-nodeset` precondition might have reset the namespace.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1433,"cache_read_input_tokens":52272,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1433},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b904b67d-27f0-44be-b761-eec61361155c","uuid":"982962bc-f882-4d14-8159-13890253cc9d","request_id":"req_011CcLRzFhTH3hd9eQz6ZfxB"}
